  "body": "My router assigns me both a local IPv4 address and a public IPv6 one. There's no ability to forwards ports, and so I want to use the IPv6 address as my node location.\r\n\r\nThat address is publicly accessible as tested using ssh from external location. Yet when I ask geth to use it, it doesn't work as expected and can't connect to any peers.\r\n\r\nAddress in this issue is randomized.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version`\r\n```\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.10.25-stable\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nGo Version: go1.19.3\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=\r\n```\r\n\r\nCL client & version: None\r\nOS & Version: `Linux 6.0.7 NixOS from 22.05.4055.fa842715565-x86_64`\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n`geth -nat=extip:ff16:90c4:d2b0:fec4:c16b:e1c5:d4ae:46e2` results in IPv6 address used for connections.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n`geth -nat=extip:ff16:90c4:d2b0:fec4:c16b:e1c5:d4ae:46e2` set both `admin.nodeInfo.ip` and `admin.nodeInfo.enode` default to `127.0.0.1` address\r\n",
